race.comment: ARTOPIA (6) should be at her peak after three runs this prep, the latest a third over 1200m at Kilcoy a month ago. Chloe Lowe has won when aboard in the past and gets the ride again. Should be hard to stop. HIT THE BUTTON (2) was far from disgraced when third last start over 1000m at Stanthorpe, beaten 2 lengths. That followed a win at Tara the start prior. Perfectly placed and is sure to make amends. QUARTER RED (4) finished eighth over 1100m at Gatton at his most recent appearance on July 10. Draws low and has to be respected while fresh. DUCHESS OF ARGYLL (10) backing up quickly after running second at Kumbia, has claims for the minors.
